<doc id="1255745" wikidata="Q5666536" url="?curid=1255745" title="Harrow Garden Village">
<text>Harrow Garden Village was a housing development in the 1930s around Rayners Lane Underground station in London, England, which until then had been a &quot;country halt&quot; on the Metropolitan line. This was Metro-land&#x27;s flagship development, begun in by E S Reid, with streets full of semi-detached houses fronted with bay windows and tiled roofs.

