<doc id="1255750" wikidata="Q16640520" url="?curid=1255750" title="Guillaume Guizot">
<text>Guillaume-Maurice Guizot (11 January 1833 - 23 November 1892) was a French essayist, translator, professor of literature and civil servant.

==Biography==
Guillaume was the son of historian and politician François Guizot and his second wife Élisa Dillon. He was the brother of Henriette Guizot de Witt.

